{
  "stem": "13251.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was watching [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the TV the other day about some kid said [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so many years the kid wasn't hugged or something like that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Never dawned on me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I grew up without that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And yet I don't think-- there's so many people that use that as an excuse for their behavior today.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And heck, I don't know any of the kids that I went with ended up being nuts or maniacs or, or violent.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, even the-- look, I was fortunate not to be in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Even the, the concentration survivors, there's no one that could have lived through worse than that, and most of them, they're, they're OK.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, they're emotionally, you know, scarred and everything else, but they don't take it out on, on, on, you know, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] behavior that's not rational or anything like that or not accepted.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I don't accept that, saying my parents' fault, something like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] That doesn't make sense to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So where are we now?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now we are-- Did you, did you and your brother kind of look to each other as sort of the guidance or, you know, to--",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Guidance?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I guess we used to talk things over, yeah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I always acknowledged him as being older and, and smarter than me, even though it was only one year.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He used to tease me a lot of times, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He has a little bit of my father's, [LAUGHS] you know, character.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, I remember when we got to be adolescents and he claimed he knew everything about sex.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'd ask him to tell me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he'd say, no, when you get older, he said to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
